{{- /*
secrets-bundle.tmpl — the decrypted secrets cache, or `{}` when GPG is not ready.

Returns the raw decrypted bundle (a JSON object mapping each `op://` URI to its
value) when the cache is available, else the literal `{}`. Callers pipe the result
through `fromJson`. The bundle is produced by the chezmoi-secrets-sync CLI and
committed at .chezmoitemplates/secrets-bundle.json.asc (GPG ciphertext).

Availability = the per-apply probe's marker (~/.config/chezmoi/gpg-cache-ready,
written iff the bundle decrypts non-interactively) AND the bundle file, both present
(stat, non-erroring). Only then is `decrypt` attempted, so a not-ready host returns
`{}` and every lookup falls back to live op via secret-read.tmpl — never a hard error
mid-render. The `stat` also guards the absolute `include` per the source rules.

Usage:
  {{ $secrets := includeTemplate "secrets-bundle.tmpl" . | fromJson }}
*/ -}}
{{- $marker := printf "%s/.config/chezmoi/gpg-cache-ready" .chezmoi.homeDir -}}
{{- $bundle := printf "%s/.chezmoitemplates/secrets-bundle.json.asc" .chezmoi.sourceDir -}}
{{- if and (stat $marker) (stat $bundle) -}}
{{- include $bundle | decrypt -}}
{{- else -}}
{}
{{- end -}}
